content: Works like all of the put put games but be sure to click on the preview pictures. The graphics are exactly that bad. Even on a 10 inch screen

This really takes me back! I was honestly worried the transition from CD-Rom game to mobile app wouldn't be so smooth and there'd be a bunch of glitches but to my pleasant surprise, the game works with no issues what-so-ever.

Seriously what did Mr. Firebird intend with a lever under a sign that just says DO NOT TOUCH!? I mean he should've just plastered a big neon sign on it that says hey kids...not that it matters since the puppy can't read it anyway

I couldn't play fatty bears game in the restaurant and I had to click many times to try and get putt putt to travel on the road. I love the game it brings back so many great childhood memories but it has a few bugs that needs fixed.

This one is not made for touch and uses a VM for a game intended for PC.  There are a lot of errors that seem to pop-up that say missing game file.  I wasn't able to get past one part of the game because of this missing file error and kept crashing.
I'm sorry I paid $5 and my daughter couldn't even play it because it kept closing. Am unable to get it to work and would really like my money back.
